title: Completely overrated. Acqua Di Gio is better.
text:
I wanted to like this fragrance, but it is completely overrated... It smells like honeydew melon + cantaloupe salad by the beach. There's nothing enticing or appealing about it. It just makes you wonder "why..?" Apart from the smell profile, the longevity/performance is just not great either. Granted, it's cheap for a reason so yeah, you'll have to spray more than you would with a higher end cologne. The problem is why spray extra so that you can smell even more like... honeydew melon + cantaloupe salad by the beach..?

There is nothing this cologne does that isn't done better by Acqua Di Gio. Save your money and buy that instead if you're looking for a 'summertime' scent.

title: Great Value for a Nice Scent
text: You get a big bottle for a reasonable cost especially compared to some of the pricey stuff out there. This is a nice clean smell that kind of reminds me of Aqua Velva. I find I don't need much of it as it's a good scent and lasts a long time, plus it stays on your skill a long time to renew the scent when your body heats up.  A lot goes a long way in terms of how strong the smell is and for how little you need in comparison to how much is in the bottle. This should last a while. This is a good one for hanging out, shopping, or a date. Be careful at work to not use too much as even though it smells good, if you use too much, it can be overpowering to yourself and others. You don't want people knowing you're coming 5 minutes before you get there. So, just an easy spritz on each arm and in the center of the chest does it for me. It's not an after shave. That would be too much for everyone's sake, at least in my humble opinion. I find my wife compliments me each time I wear this if I use just a little so she gets a whiff when I pass by and the scent is in the air. If I use a big spritz, no compliments. It's a nicer lesson on how much to use than having her complain the scent is too strong. I like to alternate use of this with Guess and Verasce Man. A rotation keeps my body from getting too used to the scent so that it doesn't really work as well--with any of them and the rotation gives me wife more chances to tell me I smell nice, which his always good to hear.  I recommend it. For me, these three replaced Soul to Soul and Soul to Soul Vintage as well as McGraw Southern Blend.

title: Even good for a blind buy, there's a *reason* this one is so popular
text: My husband picked this up for me at Christmas and I LOVE it! It's sweet, flowery and smells just a touch powdery to me. As with ANY perfume, you really have to wear it to appreciate how it works with your chemistry. It smelled good out of the package but it was even better after being on the skin. I adore how this dries down and the sillage isn't overpowering. This has become my go-to everyday perfume and I'm actually looking forward to smelling the other Princess fragrances that came after this one. Might have to start a little Vera Wang collection on the vanity :D

title: Gorgeous authentic fragrance that is a sophisticated floral, beautiful large bottle at killer price
text: I bought this blindly based on the description and customer reviews. I've never smelled this before but I needed perfume and didn't feel like paying department store prices. I really lucked out, because I find this scent to be absolutely gorgeous. It is a nice, sophisticated floral scent that's not too sweet, fruity, or girlie.  I've been randomly trying different perfumes since my Magnifique was discontinued and I can finally stop looking. I'm VERY impressed at the size of this perfume at this price. I was half expecting to receive a knock off but this is completely authentic. The bottle is beautiful.. It looks like a decoration on my vanity. This is sure  to draw compliments and inspire confidence ... It's the first thing my fiancee commented on when he got home from work. He loves  the scent on me. If you've never tried this scent, I highly recommend you do. Perfect for a grown woman who doesn't want to smell like a 16th old. And the quantity you get for the price is unbelievable!  I will be buying again when I run out.

title: Clean casual. Smells like nice blue body wash. Good for outdoor activities & chores
text:
I only wear this when I'm gonna get sweaty. Why? Because the scent is: you did a poor job rinsing off your body wash in the shower, but hey, at least you showered!

Good for going to the pool, on a run, etc. Inoffensive and shows you did something to smell nice, yet aren't dumb enough to wear something showy or expensive just to sweat it off at the most casual of casual outings.

Good for what it is, because although I'd only wear it to the pool or on a run, it's also the only fragrance of mine I would wear to the pool or on a run. So it's king of its niche, just not very versatile because for most anything else I'd rather smell like nothing than body wash.

Edit: I've actually come around to wearing this on weekend chores days. It's quite nice while cleaning, washing the car, getting groceries, etc. Clean casual is how I'd categorize it.

title: Very sweet smelling.  Definitely for the 18-25 yo range.
text: Very sweet smelling perfume, definitely very similar to VS P!nk from ~20 + years ago...not exactly but close.  I'm waiting to see how this melds with my body chemistry and after time, but so far it is just ok-too sweet.  This is very giftable, and the top pops off and becomes 2 pieces, one is a ring, seems like a size 7-its cute.  This is also a good sized perfume bottle, it is well packaged, and I was pleasantly surprised that it arrived so well packaged and not damaged or leaking.  I smell notes of citrus, apple, a hint of amber and musk, some vanilla waterlily, and CANDY. I suggest if you wear this and don't like the candy scent that seems to overpower it, spray this on just after a shower and warm it with a blow dryer as you blow-dry your hair.  So far I'm on the fence. If I decide I love it, I'll come back to change my review.  So far, it's just too sweet.

title: Smells Like The Ocean Breeze
text:
I like wearing cologne when going out and am always down to try different ones to get a chance to see what is my ultimate favorite fragrance. What I can say is that this product didn't let me down and it was refreshing to wear and I can add to my daily collection.

Quality:
The quality of this product is solid. It comes in a tall glass if you get the 6.7oz ones. This will last you for quite a long time and most likely years if you don't spray everyday. What I enjoyed about this product was that the scent isn't too strong at all. It kind of smells as if you're out on the pier near the beach with a whiff of the ocean. It isn't overpowering to a point where people will try and get away from it. The scent is actually pretty pleasant and I would wear this product on a daily basis.

Overall, solid product, and I would recommend to anyone who wants a good cologne and get it at a good price.

title: Indulge your inner 13 year old!
text: I am a 56 year old woman who probably has no business with a teeny-bopper scent, but who cares?  While shopping recently at Ulta, I thought that I would give some of their fragrances a try.  I smelled almost everything in the store; tried very hard to focus on the fragrance and not the bottle or the price--and Vera Wang Princess was the scent that I liked the most.  I liked it so much that I couldn't stop sniffing my wrist as I made my way home.  I waited a couple of days, and then went back to make sure that I still wanted to stick with Princess--it works so well with my body chemistry I felt that I just had to have it!  Checking prices--Amazon was the most reasonable, however there are a number of complaints about shoppers getting "old" fragrances. I ended up getting mine on Ebay, brand new and sealed, 3.4 oz for $28.  I am very happy with my purchase, and feel like this cold be a signature scent.  Floral and fruity, with added chocolate and vanilla notes, Princess doesn't go for the jugular, which makes it workable for casual wear.  If you like Viva La Juicy or Jessica Simpson's Fancy, this may work well for you.  I love it!

title: Needs more longevity, but otherwise near flawless.
text:
I realize there is already thousands of positive reviews about this fragrance, and anybody looking to buy this has likely already bought it, but after using for over a year (daily; at work, at home, and everywhere else I went after a shower) I feel I must add my 5 cents. To put it simply, Voyage might just be the best fresh/sporty/aquatic/clean out of shower fragrance available, period! In a way Voyage is a "gateway fragrance", allowing people who normally don't wear cologne to try it out, love it, then go shopping for something better. Perhaps this is the reason such a top-dollar smelling fragrance is priced so cheaply?

Off the bat I am going to say that the biggest negative of Voyage is the longevity. I am not going to sugar-coat or lie about this one, no matter how near-flawless the fragrance is and how much I absolutely love it, the longevity is lacking severely. But if you are into fragrances you will notice that these fresh aquatics really just don't last long, it's a limitation of the ingredients used to make these smells. Almost by definition the fresh/aquatics have next to no lasting power for some reason. No idea why that is, as I can spray just a few sprays of a heavier EDT (or EDP) and get easily a whole day of longevity. But of course the smell on those more powerful fragrances morphs into something completely different than what I smelled originally, usually not to my liking either.

Until I blindly bought this fragrance, I was NOT a cologne wearing kind of guy, with only very special occasions being the exception. I relied purely on my deodorant and shower soap to give me a fresh and clean smell. Never gave it much thought. Then one day I decided I wanted a "signature scent", something people could smell years later and think "Hey, I remember that day and time in my life when I smelled something like that". Not sure exactly what made me think of this originally, but I scoured Amazon for something I could try and see how it did for me. My first pick was Nautica Voyage. And boy, did I pick right! (even well over a year ago, this was still extremely popular with many good reviews).

I reluctantly sprayed on Voyage after my shower before work (never wore cologne to work to this point in my life), and was almost instantly reminded of the beach. Thoughts of Kramer's "beach cologne" on Seinfeld came to mind, and I immediately thought "Oh...my...goodness, this smells so good!". Fast forward to this day, and it is still my fragrance of choice, even after trying some EXTREMELY expensive and very well-liked/popular fragrances.

Voyage just does something that the others I have tried (which is a LOT) don't event scratch. It seems to do the impossible, not offend. The smell is just so.. neutral and fresh. It has this sweet, beach-like smell that is so incredibly wonderful! And the smell doesn't morph into something completely different on dry-down, it just seems to have the same signature smell from first-spray to end-of-life. Most other fragrances I have (cheap or expensive) change considerably from start to finish, but Voyage is truly a "what you smell is what you get" kind of fragrance. Which is VERY rare from my experience.

I only wish it lasted longer and had a stronger projection. I can spray on around 12 sprays and still not get through half my work day without needing to refresh (not quite as easy as it sounds, unfortunately). With the insane popularity of this cologne I am hoping for a EDP to release that won't smell different but last longer and be more potent. Might be a far fetch since this type of scent signature isn't known for it's lasting power or strength, but one can hope right? I get a whole day out of a EDT like Fahrenheit or Aqua Fahrenheit, which both have a very sweet smell to them, so why not the same lasting power from almost the exact kind of sweet smell from Voyage? (the "sweetness" smell from both of these fragrances is very close IMO).

I think the scent didn't last long on my wrists because I was wearing a long sleeved hoodie, but if you wear it on several locations of the body, making sure to apply on skin that won't be rubbing against a lot of clothing or that won't be rinsed by water (hand washing) I think it would last all day and settle into a beautiful, sweet scent that isn't loud and obnoxious.  I really loved this scent.  Also, the little ring on the top part of the perfume bottle under the crown is removable and fits my index finger perfectly.  :)  My new favorite!

I actually prefer Lucky as my daily cologne but I was wanting something different for a change and saw that this cologne received excellent ratings so I decided to give it a go. Although, it won't replace Lucky as my favorite daily cologne it is definitely a strong contender. If you'd like a summer scent that reminds you of sailing on bright blue waters then definitely give Nautica a try...

title: Not for me
text:
Everyone is different and if you've tried many different colognes by now, you should already know this. So when many reviewers mention that this cologne lasts throughout the day, I just had to try it. Me personally, I would much rather use a cologne that smelled just "okay" but lasts long rather than vice-versa. Therefore, I didn't really care how this would smell.

The smell from what I can best describe it as is having a strong and sweet kiwi fruit smell. If fruity colognes are not your thing, you might be put off by this one. This actually smells very close to Paris Hilton for Men but I'm sure for a fraction of the price.

The disappointment came in that this cologne does not last very long on my skin. I use about 3-4 sprays in the morning but by midday, it's pretty much gone. I can get like a quick sniff of it but it does not hold up to my standards of a cologne. For the price I paid for this though, I can hardly get mad. But again, everyone is different so your experience may differ from mine. You'll just have to try it.

FYI: To date, my perfect cologne remains to be Jean Paul Gaultier both in smell and longevity.

title: Haven't met anyone who disliked it
text:
"Nautica Voyage is a fresh and salty sea breeze,that carries romantic scents of coastal herbs and woods, and awakes the man's instinct to measure his power with wild nature. This is a fragrance for an active and romantic man who lives by his own rules. The face of the scent is TV host Caster Oosterhouse, a truly romantic person and a good nautician."

Nautica Voyage is extremely inexpensive, yet the scent is quite pleasing. I don't think I've met anyone who's ever disliked the smell of Nautica Voyage, it makes for a great at-work smell or perhaps to put on before going to the gym. The only downside to this scent is the longevity. I'm on my second bottle and both have struggled to last more than 4 hours. This negatively impacts my rating, as more sprays means the bottle empties more quickly than one might have originally hoped for. Overall, however, I still very much prefer this light fragrance.

title: An overlooked gem!
text:
I don't know how this perfume didn't catch on, as much as others that came out around the same time. It literally smells good on everyone and works for any occasion. The bottle and packaging are absolutely adorable and the scent is very nice. It's not overpowering, but still scented enough to last throughout the day.
As a matter of fact, I sprayed my hoody and left it at work for a couple weeks. Various co workers kept "borrowing" it to go outside, and every single one of them would comment that it smelled like me!
I love that people can still smell my signature scent after I wear something. This is a perfect scent for young or old. I'm in my 30s, but my kids love it, and so does my mom and grandma. 10/10 for Vera Wang.

Smells like sweet pickle juice and ripened hachiya persimmon. It smells sweet, with a snap of pickling spice(dill, etc. not necessarily sour though). This scent is just not for me, I was disappointed by it. In addition to not liking the scent, like others have mentioned, the scent does not last long at all, I'll mist the heck out of my jacket and shirt collar, only to have it wear off in 2 - 3 hours.

The one that I got said "Coty" on it, plus when I opened the package it smelled very moldy, I even washed the bottle with soap to get rid of it(probably had moisture in the box before it was wrapped at the factory). Overall, disappointed, not sure what to do with it.

title: Hit or miss...
text:
I bought this cologne because it was recommended by many and the very low price. I read some reviews and seemed like every so often someone got a bad bottle, a fake maybe. I decided to take the chance and hope I get a good one. I received a leaking bottle with the metal peeling from the cap, not a deal breaker as long as it smelled as good as it usually does. A few sprays and it smelled awful, like window cleaner/alcohol and a dash of cologne, it really hurts the nose. The only good thing (for this cologne) is that it does not last long, I put it on before work and asked a co-worker if she could smell it (maybe 2 hours after i put it on) and she could not unless her nose was an inch from my shirt. It was around 13 dollars so I'm glad I didn't waste more money, but this is something you find at a flea market.
Take a $15 gamble or spend a little more at a store for a legit one.

title: Is it Real or Fake? Smells Good, Whichever it is!
text:
Not sure on this one. The verdict is still out. Nothing on the bottle or the box is convincing me that this is the real stuff. I don't mind buying copy-cat stuff, but I'd like it to tell me it's copy-cat in the description. I bought directly from Amazon, so I'm assuming it's real. The UPC I received is not listed in Amazon's description.
Regardless, it smells pretty darn good. At first I didn't think it lasts too long, but it really is. Maybe it's real, maybe it's fake, all I know is I really like it.

I'll update to more stars if it passes the longevity test.

- Update -
I'm raising my satisfaction level for this. It still smells strong after a long period of time. I love how fresh and clean it feels. I'm pretty confident this is the real thing. But even if it weren't, it's still an excellent value.

title: Classic scent!
text:
I bought this blind to round out my collection as a lower priced option. Most people claim this is a great general purpose cologne, and I have to agree!

As soon as I sprayed it for the first time I instantly recognized the scent. It's a distinct beachy smell, very bright and fresh smelling. The issue I found at first is that it is actually too strong in my opinion, so I applied it again by using only one spray farther away from me, which seemed to make it very mild but still present.

While I'll probably end up using this one relatively often myself, one of the things you might need to ask yourself is if you want to use such a common scent that is mostly one note. I'm newer to colognes and even knew how common this one is as soon as I first smelled it. It's also not a terribly complex fragrance compared to some others. Not that that's a bad thing, but you might end up holding this one off for more casual affairs or if you're going out of the house for running errands or lounging around the house.

I love the smell and will continue to use it, but less than the other colognes I own.

title: A starring role in my collection but I'm still looking for "the one"
text: I don't like the piney smells typically associated with shaving gel or classic Old Spice.  I love the brighter notes of Old Spice Pure Sport, but the body spray leaves a chemical smell after the openers wear off.  This is where Nautica comes in.  I love the Blue but find it's just too weak.  I love the adventure of the Voyage N-83 the best but find it's too intense for work.  The Voyage is a happy medium and has a lot of bright simple smell with less chemical residue.  I am forever on the search for the holy grail of fragrance, but Voyage is a definite standout.  When compared side by side with Old Spice Pure Sport on a mirror, the Old Spice leaves a definite residue while the Voyage hangs around nearly as long without leaving hardly any residue.

title: Great smell! Fits the Nautica brand so well (imagine what Nautica would be...and that's exactly the smell you get)
text:
The Short and Simple
- Amazing, crisp smell
- Not too strong but not too faint either

I was looking for a new cologne and went through Amazon's top cologne and this was the #1 seller so I figured it had to be good. Read all of the reviews and it sounded like this was my kind of smell. This is definitely not your manly scent (think like dark, vanilla aromas) but more like your crisp, fresh, citrus smell. Not so citrus-y that it smells like a perfume but almost exactly what you'd expect from Nautica. The scent actually fits their image so well. I've been using it since day 1 and love it.

Be sure not to over-do the spray. I do one spray on my left wrist, then I dab my right wrist and then using both wrists, dab both sides of my neck. It's just the right amount of cologne without being too overpowering. You don't want someone to be able to smell it on you from a mile away. Not even from a foot away. You want them to be able to smell it when they get close to you.

It is more of an up close and personal fragrance, and, I would say, a bit of a unisex fragrance. I am a man, but I would even wear a perfume if I loved the smell enough lol. This fragrance dies slowly over an 8 hour period if you are concerned about that sort of thing. Nautica Voyage would make an excellent refresher to have with you wherever you are going. Enjoy this one!

title: This bottle is authentic and fresh as I checked the batch number at the bottom of the bottle with an independent website.
text: I don't understand the "fake" product reviews. These are the real deal. I even checked the manufactured fresh date on the website "checkfresh" I bought this in October/November 2016 and by entering the serial code found on the sticker at the bottom of my bottle (1 Letter, 11 numbers), I found out my batch was made in August of 2016. This tells me 2 things... THAT THE BOTTLE IS PRETTY FRESH, BUT MORE IMPORTANTLY, since IT SHOWED UP ON THE INDEPENDENT WEBSITE, THIS BOTTLE IS AUTHENTIC as the batch codes are unique. One spritz of this bottle lasts a whole day for me. It smells like a refreshing scent of stepping out of the shower with light body wash scent. IT SMELLS GOOD! A+ I did not have the opportunity to try this in the store and I went on a whim of reading all these stellar reviews so I was pleasantly surprised when I experienced the fragrance. Especially since Amazon doesn't allow refunds for perfumes/cologne as it contains flammable alcohol.

title: Probably the best value in cologne
text:
I gotta tell you, for the price and the amount of cologne you get here, this would be a good deal if it smelled like dog urine. Spoiler alert: It doesn't.

This Nautica Voyage has been a staple in our household for years. It's not the best-smelling or most unique scent in the world, but as far as value goes, it's hard to beat. Speaking strictly in terms of value, you're getting a ton of pretty decent-smelling cologne for a very reasonable price.

The scent itself won't knock you off your feet. It's not the favorite of my colognes, but one I choose when I go to work, go shopping or out to eat at the neighborhood diner. I do have some fancier cologne for the night on the town or dining at higher-end restaurants, but for a daily driver, this can't be beat. Definitely worth of five stars.

When something has a title of "voyage," I certainly don't expect it to smell like fruit. Also, this doesn't last very long at all. Two sprays and the scent is gone within an hour. If you *like* this scent, get the aftershave because that particular application lasts much longer.

title: A superb fragrance with an unholy amount of savings.
text: First I would like to say that I swear by this fragrance. I have been using it for a couple years now and I cannot count the amount of compliments I get. It has good longevity that lasts about 10 hours strong, and the sillage is just right. It doesn't quite fill a room, but follows you around arms length. People will know its you, and the best part is the scent is so light hearted that it doesn't offend when you get closer to it. Although the light scent is best for Spring and Summer, it compliments all seasons adequately. This is a must have for any collection.

title: WHEW!!! Too Strong For Me!!
text:
Heard a lot about this scent on review videos and on this site as well....so, I blind bought it. Hey! It was affordable enough so I took a chance. However.....this is way too strong for my taste. It's not a bad scent, but it's just too overpowering to my senses. I'm not a heavy sprayer or a person who "bathes" in their cologne, so that wasn't the reason. Just a test spray on my skin and I had to wash it off within an hour.
More people than not really like this scent and I'm not knocking it, it's just too strong for me.
I would recommend this, but I would also recommend you to go out and smell it at a store BEFORE you blind buy.

title: Nautica Blue & Voyage Combination Fragance Perfection!!!!
text:
I bought all three, The Classic, The Voyage and the Blue. They all smell good. But in my personal preference, the King of all three is; Voyage.

The Nautica Voyage. It smells very fancy like an cool ocean fresh but expensive elegant men perfume/cologne. All of the above in layers. For me using it in 30 degrees February winter It last a very long time 8-12+ and more if you use the right amount on you and some light spray on your clothes. You can also go light and it will last 3-6 hours depending on how much you use.

Then in second place the Nautica Blue, it smells more sweet like hinting fruity sweet and fancy with tones of cool and sporty fancy smell and very very nice. It lasts on me the just the same time length as the other Voyage.

And on third place the Classic, it smells nice but itâ€™s too muskyand woody for my personal likes, as I like it more sweet than woody but it still smells really good. I can see some older mature men liking this one better.

But the really interesting thing is that when I mix and use equal amounts of both Voyage and Blue together it creates a really incredible sweet fruity very fancy and expensive fragance thatâ€™s out of this world. It smells like cool oceanic sweet fruity sweet tones like peaches and cream with kind of pineapple hints, something really amazing to describe. I went to my daughters female doctor today and she and also her assistant who both entered at different times by themselves mentioned the really amazing smell in the room lol. Also my teenage daughter mentioned how great my perfume smelled the day before. And also another women in the elevator said â€œumm it smells really good in hereâ€ lol.

So to me itâ€™s a winner. Next time I will only buy the Nautica Voyage and the Nautica Blue, a perfect mix.

title: A perfume for older women
text:
I didn't know what this perfumed smelled like before I brought up, but instead decided to go off the many good reviews this product has.

First off, I'm around the age where I'm considered a young adult. I'm into a more modern and young smelling perfume than a product that would smell like my Grandma's perfume.

For those of you who are looking for a young smelling perfume (like I was) I would not recommend this perfume for you. Although it does not smell entirely horrible, this perfume is more fit for a middle-aged women who loves a strong, aged perfume. When I smell this perfume, I imagine an elegant older lady. That's the best way to describe the smell of this perfume, in my opinion.

This product is also non-refundable.

title: Lasting fragrance
text: I went looking for a new cologne.  I like a simple, masculine, old-fashioned fragrance.  I was drawn to Nautica Voyage, but the salesperson said it was cheap and wouldn't last.  I ended up buying two other colognes, both excellent:  Skulls and Roses and Armani Code.  But, then I still bought the bottle of the Voyage anyway (great price).  To my surprise, Voyage has lasting power no less excellent than the more expensive ones, and I love it.  It's become my regular and the other more expensive ones are "for a change."  For me, there is something almost addictive about Nautica Voyage.

title: Great Performance Great Price
text:
Scent lasted all day. I sprayed one arm twice and rubbed my other arm together at 12pm and here it is at 3am and I can still smell the scent on me. 15 hours later! Granted, the scent is barely there now, but that should give you an idea of how well this cologne works.

The scent smells great and clean. It's not abrasive in my opinion. I'd say it smells a little like the original curve cologne. But it's different enough not to be considered a copycat fragrance.

I did a blind buy with this cologne and I am very happy with my purchase. If you're getting into cologne like me, definitely try this one.

title: Smells good but didn't last long.

It does smell very good though but by the time I go out, the smell is already gone and so there is no point. I wish they could tell us how old the colognes are when we buy them, but then again that probably ain't a good marketing strategy for them. My advice for people buying this is to be wary of buying colognes when it's on sale. When it's are on sale, it could sometimes mean that they are trying to hurry and get rid of their old colognes. My old spice deodorant have a stronger smell than this.

title: I'm not sure...
text:
So I worked with this girl in 2006 that used to wear princess and I remember it was just the most intoxicating smell, but it was always kind of pricey. I saw this deal and decided to go for it, finally able to fulfill my dreams of smelling like a princess! Lol

As soon as I got the product out of the packaging, I sprayed it on the cardboard, eager to smell it again, but it just didn't smell very good to me. I can smell a cheap undertone. Like, you know when you go to CVS or Walgreens and smell the "if you like happy, you'll love delighted" perfumes? They always seem to have this one common note in the perfume that smells the same. It's like a baby powder type smell. So the princess actually came out smelling like that.

I immediately became suspicious. I found a website where I can verify batch numbers of perfumes and entered in the data and it said that the perfume was legit and was produced 03/2015. The box was also sealed professionally so it didn't look like it was tampered with... So I'm not sure!

Maybe it was left in a hot storage too long? Maybe Vera wang changed the formula? Maybe my tastes have changed? Either way, this is not the $80 perfume you were dying to buy. It's a nice smell, but it's not that high quality smell I remember so well. I'll probably just leave it in my cubicle at work until I find someone to give it to. Pass on this one and save 20 bucks.

title: Do not buy a perfume without smelling it first
text:
I am a 23 year old male and have never worn perfume/deodorant in my life. Until my landlord and I were driving to pick up some strudels and he mentioned that I should get my own perfume/spray. I think that he was indirectly telling me that I was smelly without being offensive, which I am grateful for.

I look at amazon for the best rated & most affordable cologne for men and this was it. When it arrived, I was excited... until I sprayed it and entered into state of hysterical regret.

Have you ever gone in clubs/dances and brush by many men smelling a mixture of their sweat + strong and repugnant perfume? Based on my limited experience this perfume brought back those memories. It made me think, "oh so this is what 30% of those guys were wearing?" What a shame because I do not like the smell at all.

It is my fault.

title: You get this fantastic long lasting scent from the minuscule amount that the ...
text:
A cologne that last long is hard to find. Nautica Voyage lasts a long time and the price is less then half as others. About three sprays of this scent, and you'll be able to smell it the next day. This lasts longer than Chrome or even Obsession.

You get this fantastic long lasting scent from the minuscule amount that the sprayer puts out. After all, that's why we buy expensive cologne, right? See for yourself. Go to a store. Spray a fragrance card. Smell that card in a day or two, and it will still smell like Voyage.

Spectacular aquatic scent. Fresh and clean. Somewhat akin to Cool Water, but better, and oh so long lasting. Nautica makes many fragrances, but this is far the best one I have found.

title: Adding my review...
text:
This not a fake. As long as it came from Amazon. This cologne is super hyped up if you read online reviews. And most are from the formulation with the metal cap, as alot of folks claim a reformulation ruined it. This is for the plastic cap version..... I can see why it is hyped, because it is a good everyday warm weather scent. What makes it special is the performance for the price. It projects well for a few hours, and remains in decent performance for around 4 to 5 hours. This is on par with what fresh edts are supposed to do, so nothing really special there just works like a more expensive one. The opening smells like sharp, in your face wet cucumbers to me. The heart smells like cheap, harsh, mens body wash. Very fresh and clean soapy smell. And that is not a bad thing at all, if that is what you want to smell like. I do not however get visions of being on some ocean voyage in a sail boat, that's pushing it a bit.... alot really.... on a 1 to 10 scale value for price at amazons price? 10 all the way. Projection is a 5. Longevity is a 5. Uniqueness is a 3.5. This cologne come with a recomendation from me.
Now, if you want something a bit deeper, get the equally cheap N83. Its longevity is not as good for me, but it has more of a dry down, where Voyage is very linear. Good luck!

title: Signature Frangrance :)
text:
This has been my signature fragrance since I was in high school (in college now). On me it's not sugary sweet- it has a more smoky edge to it- but just barely. It is sweet, and there are distinct notes of cocoa in it but I'm in love with the musky sweet dry down. I've always received so many compliments from it- from men and women alike :)
Guys have told me that it smells "intoxicating- like some kind of flower", and girls have told me it's warm and light but just "smells really good" haha. I'm in love with this perfume. I don't buy it here on Amazon, but after so many years of loving this perfume I felt the need to finally review it. Sometimes I combine this perfume with Mariah Carey's M (purple bottle) for a more smoky sweet/spicy smell in the winter. Most of the time though this does the trick for me ;)

I love sweet scents, gourmand are good too- but I could never wear them because they always come off too strongly on my skin. This is the perfect mix of sweet with light smoke/wood notes. Very good <3

title: Clean scent not overwhelming and great value for price
text: I purchased this for my husband originally and one day my 14 year old was leaving for school and he came up to hug me goodbye......( I know, I cherish these last few years. ) But he had obviously found a girl he wanted to impress and went to his fathers stash of cologne and selected this one. It was perfect for him, not too strong but a just a nice clean smell. I didn't pick on him, but ordered a bottle for him. For the price you cannot beat it and it's not strong enough where it would bother others. My mother purchased a more expensive cologne for him for Christmas, but he still prefers this over the more expensive one, at least for now. Highly recommend and the  customer service from Amazon is one I wish that other companies could instill.

title: This is the REAL thing and not an imitation....
text: I don't know what people are talking about. This isn't fake or an imitation. I've been using this cologne for over 20 years. It's the only one I use. This one is the same as any other one you'd buy. It smells the same and let's face it, this cologne has never lasted all day. It'll last a good 4 - 6 hours. People who say different don't know a thing. This cologne is awesome smelling. Just take it along and after 4 hours or so, take an extra spray or two and you're good. It's worth buying it here because it's selling for less money than in a department store. What a shock, huh? Department stores sell there products at a high cost to make more money. If you are 7sed to using this, buy it from here. It is NOT an imitation and if the top happens to break when it arrives, blame the shipping company. Not the cologne or Amazon. Let's grow up people.

title: Those 5 star reviews
text: So I purchased this product based on the 5 star reviews and was really excited to try it out but when it arrived it was a complete opposite from what I expected. I mean people were writing reviews as if it was one of those expensive colognes but the smell isn't good at all. It has this faint smell for few minutes and it is gone after that. If anyone is looking for a daily use body spray, I would HIGHLY recommend  "Montblanc Legend Body Spray" or you could go with "Balla for men" or "Dior Sauvage Spray Deodorant". Specially if you are in college, I would highly recommend this spray deodorants. They are light and don't feel cheap or overpowering (What's AXE?) and are suitable for everyday use. I'm not endorsing anything but based on my experience, I wouldn't recommend anyone to buy this unless you want to waste your money.

title: Cheap Toilet Cleaner Smell
text: This is the worse perfume that I have ever smelled in my life. It smells like Chrome or Acqua Di Gio with urine and toilet cleaner mixed into it. You get what you pay for. It smells too chemical like and can make you sneeze. If you are on a budget please spend  at least double the money and get a real men's fragrance online. This smells like something they give away for free in a cheap Hotel. I cannot even return. I will not give it away as a gift. It is real one from Amazon. It says made in Spain. I brought Dolce and Gabbana Light Blue Intense 3.3 fl. oz. to replace this junk. This is 100x better summer men's fragrance. But costs 3 times more than this junk. But worth the cost. I am sticking with Dolce and Gabbana brand. It will not give me a headache. Hugo Boss EDP and Man Eau Fraiche by Versace is also affordable. Seems like the people who like this Nautica Voyage are either very poor or never used any other fragrance before this one in their life.

title: For single guys, this fragrance will not help your game.  This make you smell "nice", but not "attractive".
text:
Longevity:

It lasts. It lasts for a very long time. I would come back home from work and it'd still lingers on me. And during laundry day on the weekend, the clothes still have the smell. It's an amazing longevity.

The smell:

It has strong smell of rose to it but in a masculine way. Definitely smells masculine, no hint of feminine smell. It smells clean. My first reaction upon smelling this the first time was... clean... masculine... nice... strong... some hint of floral... um.. I think I like it.

Usage:

Perfect for work. For formal settings. For everyday fragrance. It could work for a night out but not the perfect fragrance for that settings.

Final words:

How ever nice this fragrance is, it still didn't make as one of my favorite fragrances. Reasons are: 1. It smells familiar to many people. It's simply too common. 2. It's smell has slight similarity to laundry detergent. 3. For single guys, this fragrance will not help your game. This make you smell "nice", but not "attractive" or "sweet".

title: A confidence booster in a glass bottle.
text:
Always being self conscious about how I'm smelling around people, I decided to look for a cheap and reliable solution where I could see reviews of a product, rather than take a guess in a retail store.....That being said, I'm glad I made the decision because the average votes for this cologne don't lie.

Within the first week after switching to this cologne, people started commenting on how good I smell. I had never received as many compliments from any other cologne that I had purchased and even though that seems small....That was definitely a deal breaker. This cologne has a very unique smell. The only smell I can relate this to, is like walking into a Macy's store where all the bad perfumes are gone. If you're looking for that special person to notice you a little more, or if you generally want a huge confidence booster, THIS IS THE WAY TO GO.

The only cons to this product is that it is a "little" watered down. You will probably end up having to spray twice as much as you usually do with other colognes which isn't too much of a set back. It does not smell cheap; it smells very fresh, and if you use it like me and put it on every time you leave your dorm or apartment, then this will last you about 2 months. I'm going to be buying two after writing this review since I just finished my old bottle.

Only reason not to recommend this to someone, is so that you can keep this secret to yourself. Would give a 4.5/5 if I could, but you know..Amazon thinks that integers are prettier.

Hope this helped,
Cheers!
~Broccan

text:
Initial review (will be updated):
I am a female and I bought this for my beau. I just received it today and the shipping was timely. It was packaged fairly well in brown paper in a box. I was looking forward to this scent because I read "apple" and I love that smell. After the first spray I realized--this smells like men's cologne. And to me, that's not a very delightful smell. It smells generic. It smells like all the sprays of cologne I've ever used at sephora. It smells like nothing special, and it's honestly very overpowering. While I'm not too fond of the generic men's cologne smell, I'm hoping it changes a little on my boyfriend. I most of all hope he likes it. He'll be the one smelling himself afterall.
Bottle: simple, large, durable glass.
Smell: it's fresh. It's masculine. It's slightly woody and musky. It's difficult for me to pinpoint individual scents. It smells like men's cologne.
UPDATE: boyfriend is quite pleased and says it's "exactly what he wanted in a cologne." what more could I have asked?

title: Beautiful Scent, Fash Shipping
text:
I initially saw this perfume bottle and immediately thought of my sister-in-law, a self-proclaimed "Princess". She absolutely loves everything Princess. So I sprayed it in Sephora, just to see how it smelled in case I decided to get it for her. I thought "okay that's pretty nice." Then after I got home, a few hours later, I smelled my hand where the perfume had hit it, and it smelled amaaaazing. I was hooked!

I purchased a bottle for her and a bottle for me. However, at first I thought I must have been confused or purchased a fake, because it sprayed on smelling strongly like rubbing alcohol and Baby Soft. I thought, "how could I have ever liked this?? What am I going to do, giving my SIL this disgusting perfume??" But then a few moments later it began to smell like water-lily and apricot. I thought, "okay, this is better but still not what I thought it would be..." After a couple of hours, it dried down into a beautiful sugary smell with vanilla and chocolate undertones. I then realized that this WAS the perfume I had originally fallen for in Sephora, but that it changes its smell throughout the day until it finally becomes this beautiful base scent.

I'm glad I purchased this perfume on Amazon. I got a much cheaper price, and the shipping was extremely fast - I ordered it on Friday evening and it was in my hands Monday evening.

I think this will become my signature daytime/office scent. It gets really hot here in Florida and so I can't wear any of my usual spicy, musky, oriental scents during the day after March. I also can't wait to give my SIL her bottle for Mother's Day. I'm sure she will love it and love sharing it with her own daughter, the "little Princess".

*I'd like to add one thing - I went to Sephora after this purchase and smelled Princess while there. I sprayed it directly on my wrist. It had the EXACT scent, even the alcohol-type scent when you first spray. Completely identical, so rest assured that this product is NOT a fake.

title: Long lasting. Better than Nautica Blue
text:
I've tried Nautica blue, island voyage, and voyage.
This is certainly better than Nautica Blue. It's very similar to island voyage. However, it certainly lasts a long time. It is a mellow fresh scent. It feels a lot more "real" than blue did. It's not the manliest thing around but it is a worthwhile upgrade to Nautica blue. The big bottle choice is actually massive compared to the one you find at wally world and so it is certainly a good deal. If I had to guess the small choice is actually the large option at wally world. I like it. Out of the three, I think this may hit the sweet spot by a small margin over island voyage for scent. What is interesting was that Blue was my everyday scent, and I think I probably won't go back to it.
The bottle itself looks very well made and looks classy.
My only complaint is that a little goes a long way with this one so you have to be careful with the amount you use per spray if you want to use more than a spray or two as it is potent.

title: My favorite fragrance for daily wear
text:
I was recommended Nautica Voyage by a friend of mine who loves collecting fragrances. Turned out to be one of the best I've tried in years.

It's a lovely fresh fragrance... quite pleasant, not overbearingly strong, but 'just right'. lingers on for a long time... For me, it has been hard to find something that is mild, pleasant, long-lasting and yet economical. The mild ones were either too mild or too short-lasting, and the strong ones are too overbearing. I get a headache if I wear such fragrances too long.
Also the good ones usually cost a lot. This one - Nautica Voyage, however was one perfume that I felt was just right. And great value for money!

A cousin of mine to whom I gifted this was also all praise for it.

All in all, 5 stars.

Itâ€™s a sweet scent. Itâ€™s not like a musk, aftershave type of scent. To describe it, I would consider Tommy Hilfiger (for men, silver lid, clear bottle, black lettering), Curve (for men, green bottle, gold lettering) to be sweet scents, but is distinctively different and not in a bad way.

Itâ€™s not crazy overpowering with a single pump or two, but I wouldnâ€™t go more than thatâ€¦ unless you want the entire room to know the instant you walk thru the door.. you know the type of people Iâ€™m talking about.

I definitely recommend this, and Iâ€™ll be a return customer.

title: Smells like cleaning product.
text:
Iâ€™ve been looking for this in stores for a while but I havenâ€™t been able to find it. Given that this is widely regarded as one of the best affordable frags on the market I went ahead and bought it without trying it out. Unfortunately after receiving it I quickly realized itâ€™s not for me. The scent is very synthetic. It reminds me of generic cleaning products. At first I thought that maybe thatâ€™s just how this frag opens and it would mellow out after time but the scent is very linear.

That said, if you do happen to like the scent this is a great performer. The longevity and projection are very good. In fact, I will begrudgingly admit that they are better than my current favorite frag from YSL, which retails for nearly 6 times as much. But, if you donâ€™t like the scent, then no amount of performance is going to do you any good.

Bottom line. If youâ€™ve tried it and know you like it then you already know itâ€™s a good performer at a great price. If you have not, I strongly suggest you test it before you buy. Unfortunately Amazon will not let me return this so Iâ€™m stuck with a large bottle of juice I will never use.

title: New favorite perfume-  Totally love it
text:
New FAVORITE perfume. I see some of the more commonly asked question, like describing what it smells like, which is so tricky. But here's some things that come to my mind:

- It's NOT "candy" scented like I've seen some imply. To me, its "sweet" smelling for sure, but I don't think of candy. I think more of a floral sweet. It doesn't smell like roses, but if you can imagine how that strong rose smell is "sweet", that's how I'd describe the potency. Strong and sweet.
- It does last for hours and hours and the scent DOES change, but not drastically. It's more overpowering at first, and then it simmers down. I can take a deep breathe right now and still smell the application I put on about 2 hours ago from my neck.
- I spray this on my sheets and pillows and it lightens up my room. And it stays fresh and sweet for days. I have gotten so many random compliments of friends walking by my room, or coming in and saying "Is that a candle? An air freshner? What is that!"

LOVE IT!!

I often get compliments on how wonderful I smell but that it is not overwhelming.

title: Cheap and Good
text:
To The Point: If you like Dolce and Gabbana Light Blue this is similar and I feel like is slightly better. Just spend the $20

If you're like me you may have a collection of colognes typically far more expensive than this, however, for $20 this is a good performer.

Initially when I first sprayed it I got a heavy heavy scent of hand sanitizer and was like oh damn here goes a fake. But that's only because it's cheap AF.

A few minutes later it went away and opened up to my surprise a pretty clean scent. Nothing amazing. But to me it smells fresh and like a oceanic musk? It is good.

$20 just buy it. It's nothing crazy like Aventus or Sauvage, but for $20 again $20 it's awesome. I didn't really have many "fresh and clean" scent in my collection so this is a nice cheap addition.

title: A favorite at a great price!
text:
This is my favorite perfume, which I wear as my signature scent. Don't let the "little girl" bottle fool you - this is a very sophisticated light floral scent with hints of fruit and vanilla, suitable for a woman of any age. It is VERY light. If you like heavier scents this may not be for you. The top note fades quickly, and after that it's a very subtle scent. But anything that "clings" for too long gives me headaches anyway. You can still smell it on the skin, but it does not "broadcast". Because I think perfume should be a reward, not an announcement, that's fine with me.

The price is fantastic, and the perfume arrived quickly. Couldn't be more pleased.

title: This IS the real thing people!!!
text: Just from working in perfumes and colognes for years, I have to say that this product is the real thing. Fyi, an eu, de perfume has more of the rich oils, hence the scent will last longer on your skin. This is the eu, de toilette which has more alcohol in it and evaporates more quickly. So if you want the eu, de toilette to last longer, first put on the lotion or cream, then add your eu, de toilette. You don't really need to with an eu, de perfume because it is more concentrated and usually alot more expensive. So people, do not listen to the negative reviews saying that the scent does not last and it's fake, because,  IT IS NOT! I love this scent so much and wanted to clear up any misconceptions on this perfume.

text: This item seems diluted and does not meet the standard of Nautica Voyage by Nautica for Men.  I previously purchased Nautica Voyage (in the past 2 years from a department store) and still have some of the product.  I compared the recent purchase of NV that I received from my AMAZON purchase with the same product purchased from a department store and found the AMAZON NV to have a faint fragrance and essentially not be the same product that I had purchased from the department store (Although the name is identical).  I am disappointed and this makes me suspicious of online products and hesitant to make similar future purchases online.  Maybe it makes me suspicious of the quality of Nautica Voyage?  Either way - something is not consistent.

title: Best Bang for your Buck!
text: A "best bang for your buck" fragrance, Nautica Voyage is easily worth the 20 dollars or so that you'd spend to buy a large bottle. The apple, lotus, and mimosa notes blend very nicely to create a perfect casual summer cologne. Voyage goes on a little scratchy at first, but after 15 minutes or so it settles in and creates a beautiful scent trail. It's citrusy, with just enough sweetness to take the edge off, and the right kind of florals to round it out. What I like most about Voyage is that there's this root-beer like fizz in the mix of it all as well. What you ultimately get is an appealing and addictive accord that persists for several hours before settling into a skin scent around the 3 to 5 hour mark. Projection is average. Voyage is appropriate for any age and best suited for Spring and Summer.

title: their customer service is wonderful. Now
text:
Let me just start by saying, ANY perfume purchased directly from Amazon LLC (Prime) is legit. Just because you purchase from Amazon website, does not mean you are buying directly from Amazon itself. Many sellers go THROUGH Amazon to sell their merchandise. Personally, I would never buy perfume from any of these sellers because perfumes could be watered down, counterfeit, etc. & perfume is just way too expensive for me to gamble with. I trust Amazon and have never had a problem with receiving anything but REAL perfume. Also, their customer service is wonderful. Now, on to the product...

Vera Wang Princess is a beautifully developed perfume, and way more complex than anything a middle schooler or tween would wear. It is surprisingly more mature than one would expect. I am 20, and I do not BY ANY MEANS wear anything old ladyish. While i do try to keep a variety of perfumes on hand, I cannot stand anything too florally or musky. Also, I am pregnant and Princess is one of the few perfumes I can wear almost daily without becoming nauseous. I am one of those people who perfumes do not last long at all on my skin. They also don't do much developing once there. I can smell Princess on my clothes weeks after applying it. I wore it to work last night (I do 12 hour shifts at a nursing home) and could not only smell it the entire time I was there, but after I got home as well giving it a total longevity of 16 hours on my skin. People within about a foot of me could smell me, but by no means was the scent overwhelming or offensive. Vera Wang's princess is for all ages. It is girly, feminine, and a bit innocent but never juvenile. It is a good signature or everyday perfume. Could easily be worn on a date or any occasion, really. I cannot say enough good things about this perfume. Amazon has the best price.

It came packaged like others I've purchased but it was most definitely NOT the same VW Princess I've used in the past.  I was actually surprised by the inexpensive price for this on Amazon when I saw it and thought I was getting a REALLY great deal for one of my favorites. Not so. Oddly, I'd also purchased some Vanilla Fields on Amazon too a few weeks before this and while the product liquid itself was darkly discolored (a sign of heat exposure and/or aged product), it did have a normal scent and a lingering that was entirely expected. I would NOT recommend and will not be buying again.

As a customer with minimal knowledge or purchase history in the scent industry, I started to look around and see what popular colognes are being sold.

After reviewing some expensive products, I was skeptical upon purchasing a more affordable cologne from a brand that I am most familiar with producing clothes.

I was relieved and very impressed when I received this well packaged, fancy looking bottle.

Nautical voyage is very effective in producing a soft, ocean blossom sent with a sweet apple undertone and a touch of earthiness to produce a fresh, ocean like frangrance

Three pumps will leave a long lasting, soft scent that is noticeable but not too pungent.

Worth the money. Iâ€™ll be keeping this around as I expand on my collection.

title: It's great!
text:
I'm rewriting my review because initially I didn't like this very much. I felt like the guava was too strong, and dominated the fragrance. I didn't get much chocolate which was disappointing.

But after using this a few more times I fell in love with it. And this happened with some other perfumes as well. I don't know if my chemistry changes on a frequent basis, or if I just get used to the perfume? Maybe a combination of both. Whatever happened, I love this now!!! It's so soft and sweet, and just a pleasant smell.

I do detect a little chocolate and vanilla and lots of guava, but now I love the blending of the three. Definitely happy with my blind purchase.

title: The Perfect, Inoffensive Work Fragrance
text: Needing an inexpensive office fragrance, I looked up a lot of reviews online, and many of them directed me to Nautica Voyage. As something I can spritz myself with as I'm running out the door, this stuff is awesome. I've gotten lots of compliments from co-workers with this, and my customers seem to appreciate it to. It smells fresh, clean, and while I don't really get the apple note, it does have a crispness to it that reminds me of a cool day on the east coast. It barely lasts a full 8-hour shift, but it's so cheap, I don't feel guilty about spraying more. I even use it as an air freshener at home sometimes, because I know I can just buy more. There's literally no reason NOT to get this, IMO.

title: Nothing impressive
text: I'd had Princess of my "blind list" for a while and finally decided to purchase it, again based off the number of positive reviews I'd read about it. I really need to stop doing that and start smelling before I buy, because this was unfortunately another flop. On the initial spray, I could sense nothing but florals and powder. As it dried down, it smelled like a mixture of chocolate and vanilla pudding. I will admit, I did enjoy it much more after the dry down, but not enough to earn a "like" here. A few past reviews mentioned they thought Princess smelled similar to Britney Spears Fantasy. Apologies, but I disagree 110%. Fantasy is much sweeter, stronger, and longer lasting, where Princess is more light, powdery, and easily fading (only lasted about 2 hours on me). I've worn Fantasy for years, and in no way do I feel it smells anything like Princess. On the plus side, the bottle is gorgeous. I love how you can stand it up or lay it flat. While I'm not a really huge fan of this, I'm going to keep it in my collection for a bit before offering it to a friend. Going to try my best to see if I can let it grow on me, but I doubt it'll happen.

title: It smelled awful. Like someone let a bottle of Windex ferment on a hot beach for a few weeks
text:
Short answer: It smells awful. Do not buy it.

Long answer: Colognes are personal. They interact with your personal body chemistry and will smell differently for different people and at different times. Where you spray it (side of neck, chest, on clothes, on skin), how much you put on (one spray or 3), when you put it on (after a shower in the morning, after working out, before going out at night). All of these factors will influence how it smells. Not to mention the chance you receive a knock off as opposed to the real product.

So, that being said, Nautica Voyage for men did not smell good on me. It did not smell ok on me. It smelled awful. Like someone let a bottle of Windex ferment on a hot beach for a few weeks. Maybe it was me. Maybe it was one of those scents that do not work well with me. Maybe. All I know is that it was unusable. I tried. Really I did. I used it at different times, on different parts of my body and with varying amounts. Nothing helped. It still smelled like gasoline with chemical "beach smell" added in.

I ended up contacting the Amazon support center and explaining the situation. They were awesome. Refunded my order and sent me another one (I explained that it may have been a knockoff). title: Greater starter cologne for a young man!
text:
I'm a 22 year old college student who hasn't really started to wear cologne. Well I'm about to graduate from school and I've got myself a big boy internship. I wear dress shoes and ties and I think it's about time for me to also grow out of my teenage body sprays (axe/old spice). I had very mixed feelings about cologne in general. It always felt like something only older men wear, like something that was too expensive. I've also had some bad run-ins with people who spray way too much fragrance and could clear a room.

I decided to check to see what kind of products amazon had. Nautica Voyage was and still is sitting at the Number #1 best seller in Men's Cologne, so I though I'd give it a try. I was not disappointed. Overall, I'm ecstatic about this fragrance. I'm not a scent connoisseur or anything but it smells great. I would almost describe it as taking a shower after laying out on the beach. It's light and airy, but also distinctly masculine. It's not overpowering in any way and I've worn it to work, school, and social functions without any objection. Be sure to only do a few sprays though. (I two sprays on the front of my wrists and rub it into my neck/chest).

My girlfriend loves it. Every time she hugs me now, she takes an extra second to smell my chest. I've also received a few compliments from friends (if they get close enough to smell it).

I was a bit concerned because of all of the reviews about fake products. I went with the default seller and everything seems fine. My bottle does have a plastic cap, but has a serial number on the bottom sticker. The smell also seems legit and lasts for quite awhile. The concern about the cap might just be an updated bottle design.

-Overall, I'm glad I bought it. For the cheap price, I consider it a great starter cologne. It's a fragrance that seems to work in almost every situation and I have yet to meet a person who hasn't liked it. If you find this review helpful, please hit the "Yes" button below. Also feel free to let me know if you have any questions and I'll be happy to answer them!

title: Pristine, clean scent that is a breath of fresh air.
text:
In my short 27 years I have only used two scents on an ongoing basis (let's not discuss the AXE body spray craze we all went through in high school). These were Curve for Men by Liz Claiborne and Acqua di Gio by Giorgio Armani.

Curve I wore as I was going through puberty and matured throughout high school. I used it for a few years in college as well as I always seemed to get compliments on it. As my tastes grew I then got hooked on di Gio and used it up until now. I was getting a bit tired of it and actually stopped using cologne for about a year or two. I figured I would experiment and try something new as I did miss those two sprays in the morning after a shower which had me smelling great all day.

I picked up Voyage by Nautica as it was at a very decent price and it seemed to have favorable reviews. They were for the most part spot on. This is a very fresh, clean scent, nearly akin to a fresh set of laundry after retrieving it from the dryer. I asked my girlfriend who for 6 years has known me to wear di Gio, and she loves it. She likes the fresh scent and says its literally a breath of fresh air.

If you're looking to experiment, try this cologne out. I'm not a connoisseur by any means but I think its a fresh scent that anyone could go with. And at this price point you're not really losing out. As previous reviews have stated make sure you have the authenticity sticker at the bottom of the bottle. The risk of getting a lemon is there but it seems like the majority of the bottles are authentic!

title: I loved it so much I immediately purchased a second for ...
text:
I have purchased two of these. After buying the first which I had planned on keeping at work, I loved it so much I immediately purchased a second for home. The one that I loved had a single piece plastic cap, and the smell was VERY nice and lasted (strongly) all day, and several days following until the shirt was washed. The second one I ordered has a cap which was heavy metal, which only covered the nozzle. It smelled very similar, but not quite the same, and only lasts maybe 3-5 hours before becoming very faint. Both of these bottles came in identical shrink wrapped boxes, same bottle, both fulfilled by Amazon, and both had stickers on them with 4 digit codes on the bottom- the only difference being the caps, and the obviously different formulas/strengths.

I'm not sure what I'll end up doing once these run out, but if I get another bottle like the second one I ordered, I will return it and switch to a difference cologne.

Love this scent! Wearing it for several years now.

There are many misleading comments on Amazon. Most of them sound like this â€“ â€œOh, it is a fake! Itâ€™s a watered down version! Donâ€™t buy!â€ When you write such comments, please, also mention from whish seller did you bought this fragrance. This is a cheap, under 20$, fragrance and I am sure no one needs trouble to make a fake.

The first bottle I ordered in 2019 from Amazon (seller Amazon) and the second one I ordered few days ago (seller Amazon). The first bottle is made in US and the new one is made in Spain for EU market. Bottles are identical, scent is identical, and both last around 7-8 hours depending on your skin type, which is very good for EDT. I did not notice any changes in performance. Both of them are original, but made for different markets - US and EU. Stop misleading people! This fragrance is one of the best in its class in terms of price / quality ratio!

title: Very pleasant smell, best for spring ambience
text: I am in college and found this cologne to be one of the best value colognes. I received this in a well packaged box with no issues. I don't put on cologne every day, more like once or twice a week with two to three spritz each time. With that rate, it seems like this would definitely last me more than a year, maybe two. The smell is a slightly sweet smell, very pleasant. I get some compliments using this, and this is not overbearing at all. The scent lasts for most of the day, and sometimes I smell it in the old clothes I wore from previous use.  I'd recommend this for a spring type of feel. It doesn't seem to have much musk. I have several colognes, but I am no expert on scents so take this review with a grain of salt. This is still my favorite budget cologne.

text:
I have just recently decided to get into the habit of dressing better and fragrances. While I'm not the marketed age range for this fragrance, I talked to many friends and have seen many Youtubers recommend this . I decided to give it a try. Let me tell you I love it. Its a great work or Spring time cologne,

The reviewers were correct. I love the fresh scent and the longevity last at least 6 to 8 hours. Its not too weak but not too strong either. The price for this stuff is excellent as well. This is a great daytime scent for work . Everyman man should have this in their collection.

The company who shipped this too me as excellent as well. Only reason I don't give this a 5 star, is because I know their are better fragrances out there. But for a safe, reliable scent..This stuff rocks. My only regret is discovering this late in life . But better late than never.

title: Got a fake bottle, it was horrible. Be cautious when buying this product.
text: I ordered this a couple of months ago and got my money back within a week, just forgot to post a review about it. I got a fake bottle of perfume, and I knew it immediately after opening the box. It was the wrong color. It did not smell as good as it is supposed to, I have been using this perfume for years. It smelled like a Hint of Nautica Voyage, but mostly smelled like rubbing alcohol. It was not good. And it didn't last as long as real Nautica Voyage. I could spray myself once in the morning and I would smell amazing all day, but this stuff I had to reapply multiple times in one day to smell somewhat like the Nautica Voyage I loved. I compared everything about this new bottle to what I had left from my old bottle and it was all wrong. The sticker on the bottom was wrong, there was no serial number, it was a fake. You can't physically return this item, but you can get your money back. The refund process was quick and simple and I got my money back within a week. I don't even know what I did with this unfortunate bottle of 'perfume'. I think I threw it away or lost it in the back of my bathroom closet, but I used it for 2 days and that was it. With the amount of positive 5 star reviews you would think it would be safe to buy this product, but apparently you can, and will, get a fake and gross bottle of perfume in stead. Safer to just buy it when it's on sale in stores.

title: Amazing scent and feel
text:
One of the first thing I noticed about this cologne is the smoothness felt when placed on your skin. I have other more expensive colognes that are initially pungent and you feel the alcohol aggressively in your nose and on your skin, this is not the case with this cologne at all and I am impressed by it. The scent also does not initially smell like alcohol at all.

The scent is HEAVENLY! I've bought other colognes with high expectations because they were recommended or because they are of a brand name or expensive price or nostalgia and I've been very let down. It was the contrary with this one, I didn't expect much for 6 ounces and such a low price and the smell is amazing! I bought 6 ounces because of the value compared to 3 ounces and the glowing reviews. It's such a great blend it's difficult to pick out what smells make up the overall fragrance. It does smell "like the ocean" in a very positive way. It doesn't smell too heavy at all but it's not too light either. Also, I tend to hate sweet smells but the amount of sweetness in this scent is almost non distinguishable. I would not have noticed it unless I would have read about it and again, it's so very well blended it's difficult to pick it apart. One can also immediately tell it's a man's scent without it being overbearingly so and it does not have any floral smell.

I'm a sucker for blue and for the ocean so maybe that might influence also but such amazing reviews were not wrong in my case. The bottle is attractive as well as the blue color of the fragrance. I'm extremely happy with my purchase and this is by far my favorite scent now not because of brand name, nostalgia or price but because the scent is so fascinatingly great and I enjoy it even wearing it while I'm alone.

title: Mine wasn't genuine
text: I am disappointed.  I bought one of these from Amazon and it is not genuine (I compared it to the one from the department store I bought a couple of years ago).  I looked for the tell-tale signs...turn it upside down and look at the bottom.  A genuine Nautica will have a Nautica sticker on it (it will say 'Nautica Voyage' in big letters).  It should also have some sort of stamp of numbers (my original Nautica from the store had 4 numbers in black dot ink).  Also, my bottle from Amazon was poorly made; the bottom of the inside is not straight and quite noticeable.  Lastly, the Amazon bottle smells slightly off after an hour.  I also had my wife smell my shirt where I sprayed different spots with the 'real' bottle and the bottle from Amazon...she quickly identified the imposter.

I tried some on my forearm first, to see if I can go full body or if I'll just have to give it away. My first use, my sister hated it and like I said it was different so wasn't too sure if I liked it yet, but it was alright to me. On my second use I found it was good enough for me; I actually like it and it lasted almost all day, providing you don't sweat a lot, cause I don't think this one will hold up for a rigorous day... So overall I would say it's a very good cologne especially for the price, you can't go wrong... But like I said, it all depends on u'r body chemistry.

title: Smells great, lasts a long time and a good price
text:
At first I was a bit skeptical about the purchase, what with all the people saying they got a fake version or something like that, so I wasn't sure what I would receive. Upon receiving it I was sure it was real since it was in a sealed box and the bottle had the proper stickers on it with a good labeled cap.

Really glad I decided to try this out because I love it. It has a very "fresh", fruity wood smell to it. It's not too overpowering either, has a nice subtle way about it. You can always apply more if you want a stronger aroma but a couple of sprays after a shower will last a good amount of time, I'd say like 4-6 hours, maybe more depending on how much you use.

All in all a great purchase, especially at this price. Definitely recommend.

title: Wow....Just Wow
text:
I've never written an Amazon review before. That's how floored I am by this fragrance. Everything about it is just wonderful and pleasant.

The second I took the cap off I couldn't help but smile. That is how pleasant the scent it. I sprayed one spritz into the cap and aired it out which only further cemented my first impressions. I've only worn it out once so far, but boy could I not stop smiling and feeling confident all day for the life of me.

The bottle is lovely and high quality (in my opinion) for how cheap it all is. Presentation pairs perfectly for the scent which is even lovelier. I would absolutely 110% recommend this fragrance.

Scents are interesting because everyone has a different perspective of them. Some people like the smell of fresh cut grass, others hate it. Where one person smells a plain cup of coffee, another smells that scent and pictures home where their dad would have the same cup of coffee every morning.

So that being said, I would have to describe this fragrance as the after shower glow smell. I don't mean immediately coming out of the shower. And I definitely don't mean that this scent smells like any generic shower gel. This fragrance is the definition of fresh and clean. It smells like how you smell and feel 10-20 minutes after stepping out of the shower. Crisp, refreshed, clean, confident. It does this while also smelling like a man taking a leisurely stroll down the docks, observing all the yachts that are tied up.

Stop reading reviews and buy this fragrance, you will not be disappointed. And if on the off chance you are, it was only $20 and I can guarantee you can find somebody in your life that would love to have this fragrance gifted to them, or would happily buy it from you for the same price you paid for it.

title: Great price, not the same potency as older bottles.
text: I bought this bottle of Nautica Voyage to replace the bottle that I am almost out of that I purchased from Macy's. When I saw the price I thought how can you go wrong but after getting the bottle I have experienced what many others have experienced here on amazon where the scent is not exactly the same. The bottle I had received is properly marked by Nautica, it had the sticker on the bottom of the bottle and is exactly the same as the one I bought from Macy's and it came in the correct box. However after spraying the cologne from amazon you can tell the scent is not the same as the one I have from Macy's. This one from amazon is noticeably lighter smell to it, and though it pretty much smells the same in terms of the scent, to me the bottle from amazon has a slightly more alcohol smell to it. I do not know if this is cause Nautica has changed how they made their cologne, or if this what others on here suggest is watered down but I do know it is just not the same as my older bottle from Macy's, draw your own conclusions. Overall to get the same effect as my older bottle I may have to spray more, and maybe in in the future I am going to have to try it in the store again to see if it changed before I buy it again on amazon.

title: Incredible Bargain
text:
This cologne was great. Nice bottle, generous size and it smelled great. It did last the entire day also. I'm not sure why some people on here think this was a fake. Although this cologne was a great deal, it's not one of the top dollar colognes to begin with and in my experience, those are the only one that anyone would waste time and money faking.

That being said, my only issue was that I did not like the smell on me personally. There are just some colognes that start to annoy me once I wear them for a while. This was one of them, maybe because the strength of the cologne seemed to stay consistent the entire day (I wear it under my clothes and on my skin) or maybe because it just didn't mix well with my particular body chemistry.

But I imagine the majority of people will like this cologne and I think for the money it was a fantastic deal.

title: Meh
text: Not my bag, just too boring and typical.  The sort of scent that is like 1000 others in the same price range and makes the ladies walk on by to the guy wearing any scent from Cerutti or Versace.  I bought this in the search for a backup everyday scent.  Thallium Blue is my starter and still the best, lowest priced men's fragrance one can buy in my humble opinion, if it jives with your body chemistry.  I read reviews and had hopes that this might be the one to mix things up a little with the everyday scent, but nothing doing.  It might be great for some and gets some 5 stars, but I've bought men's fragrances online that had thousands of five-star reviews and smelled like an old ladies perfume. It's a gamble when you buy scent online with no way to check it out first. All you can do is give it a shot and don't spend too much money on anything you haven't checked out at a brick-and-mortar store and confirmed you like. This one you can check out at Walmart, which should say it all with regard to how typical and boring this scent is.

title: Bottom Line: Cucumbers & Salt
text:
Yes this is a cheap, decent quality, mass-appealing blue fragrance. However, in my opinion it is not very versatile in that the scent isn't generic or "shower gel" enough to use across the board. The scent is heavily dominated by cucumber and salt. Too much so in my opinion.

This cologne is best used in summer around beachy environments, or as a touch up when you're leaving the gym, or in the middle of a long work day. I wouldn't use it for much else, and it's worth noting that I gave up on it, and gave the rest of the bottle to my brother.
