title: Not the same Quality as older Products Ordered
text:
Disappointed,
Where is the company getting this product from?
I have been purchasing this product for years and I was able to notice the change of the scent, scent strength and lasting.
In the last 4 products I received the fragrance is not strong enough as originals products.
As soon is applied to the skin, the aroma is thin and almost gone, in order to really smell the product you need to be really close to the body surface where you applied the cologne (it is like rubbing alcohol with some level of scent).
I cannot state that is FAKE because I am not expert, but for sure is not as good as products from other years.
My wife was able to tell the difference really quick and asked me if I change the type of cologne because for her it was a different product.
I confirmed the product differences in the dedicated stores where the "same" product is available.
Value is not the same as products from years ago, I have to use tons of the product to have the same level of scent from me. For my wife maybe I will need to go and buy in another place.

title: Like sailing on a boat.
text:
Years ago, a friend gave me Nautica Voyage on a whim, and I liked it. When I ran out, I went and bought a bigger bottle recently.

The reason I bought it again is that it smells absolutely amazing. After it opens with a mixture of apple and mint, it gradually shifts to being an aquatic fragrance that is reminiscent of an open sea.

Howwever, the major drawback of this fragrance is that longevity is terrible. While I expect aquatic EDT fragrances to lack staying power, Voyage is particularly bad. You will need to reapply it after four hours, and less time in the winter months outdoors.

That aside, Voyage definitely works well in the gym, or in an office/school environment, and is also a reasonable evening or date night fragrance in the summer.

Furthermore, despite the concerns of longevity, the price point (which is very affordable) and the excellent smell make Voyage a great fragrance to own or have on hand.

title: Great Aquatic Summertime Cologne.
text:
Loved the Scent, Longevity, and Cost. Ocean type scents usually don't last that long, but with this Cologne you can expect 7-9 hours, with about a 3 hour projection. For only around $15 dollars (I bought it for $12 on sale) this product is definitely a steal.

You get an aquatic scent, with a hint of apple and lotus. Pretty masculine, something I'd wear to a high-prestige interview or something of that tier. I often get compliments on it when I wear it.

Hint: A little goes a long way. I usually do 2 sprays on the neck and 1 spray for one wrist, and transfer it to the other one. You get a nice scent that lasts throughout the day without being offensive or too strong. It gives that great smell when you walk past somebody, or when they stand close. Really enhances your natural scent.

A bottle would probably last you around a year, unless you're a cologne freak.

title: Scent has definitely changed !
text:
I am extremely disappointed with this product as well as the inability to receive a refund or replacement. I first ordered this specific scent about 6 months ago and love it, so thought to order another one in time for the holidays. Prior to doing so, I read the comments for some reason and found people complaining of the scent being very faint and/or smelling like alcohol. But again, I ordered this product before so I ignored and proceeded. Well i definitely should have followed my instinct and listened to the reviews. The â€œcologneâ€ scent is basically non existent as rubbing alcohol is the only smell present. Believing I was imagining things I sprayed it on myself, my clothes and a towel yet the smell was not apparent on anything. I even took a shower, put on fresh clothes and doused myself in the cologne, yet my girlfriend could only â€œmaybeâ€ smell it. Yet, when spraying my original
Bottle which has only a small amount left, the difference is night and day. I understand that things happen and with mass production issues like this are not unheard of. But, this added with the inability to return OR receive a replacement is enough for me to not give it another try in the future.

title: Great Value
text:
This review is for the Nautica Voyage 100ml/3.3oz eau de toilette. Itâ€™s important to know exactly what weâ€™re talking about here.

The scent is a â€œyoungâ€ one. Itâ€™s fresh and clean with some spice notes. Itâ€™s better suited to younger men. The scent is good, better than average. That makes the $17 an EXCELLENT value for the quality of the scent.

I realize, â€œgood, better than averageâ€ is a very subjective description but, letâ€™s be real, when weâ€™re talking about scents itâ€™s all subjective. I think you can understand where Iâ€™m coming from. I would say â€œokayâ€ or average would be something like Old Spice Original or BRUT. Better than â€œgoodâ€ starts to get even more subjective relying heavily on individual tastes.

This â€œgood, better than averageâ€ scent is at or below most â€œokayâ€ prices. That makes it a great value. If youâ€™re lucky it may be one of your favorite scents for cheap! If youâ€™re like me it may be a great â€œevery dayâ€ value to wear to work while saving your favorite fragrances for nicer occasions.

The other big feature, besides scent, is longevity. It shines here too. This is an â€œeau de toiletteâ€ fragrance. As such it is one of the least concentrated types of fragrances. It is meant to be light and doesnâ€™t typically have great longevity. This one actually has very good longevity, though.

The fragrance develops, of course. It is different at 5 min, 1 hour & 5 hours. But it is still there after 8 hours! That is exceptionally rare for eau de toilette fragrances. That kind of longevity for $17 also makes it an excellent value.

title: High Value product
text:
[[VIDEOID:ed97f71ec640b3c8119315637d6ab75c]] Nautica Voyage is a cologne that has gained popularity among men for its fresh and invigorating scent. The fragrance is created by Nautica, a well-known brand in the world of fashion, and is designed to capture the spirit of the sea, making it an ideal choice for those who love the outdoors.

The scent of Nautica Voyage is a blend of fresh and aquatic notes, making it a perfect fragrance for spring and summer. The top notes include cool green leaf and apple, which give it a crisp and refreshing scent. The heart notes are a blend of mimosa and lotus, which add a floral touch to the fragrance. The base notes are a mix of musk, amber, and cedarwood, which give the fragrance a warm and earthy undertone.

The longevity of Nautica Voyage is moderate, lasting for around 4-5 hours on the skin. However, the sillage or projection is quite good, making it a noticeable fragrance without being overpowering.

The bottle design of Nautica Voyage is sleek and elegant, with a transparent blue glass bottle and silver cap. The design is simple yet sophisticated, reflecting the essence of the fragrance perfectly.

Overall, Nautica Voyage is a refreshing and versatile cologne that can be worn casually or for more formal occasions. Its blend of fresh and aquatic notes make it a perfect fragrance for the warm weather, and its moderate longevity and good sillage make it a great choice for everyday wear. If you're looking for a fragrance that embodies the spirit of the sea, Nautica Voyage is definitely worth trying out.

title: The real deal at a great price
text: I was worried about the authenticity of this after reading the bad reviews, but it is definitely the real deal. For people concerned that the top is loose, those are the secret rings it comes with. And this scent is supposed to have gold rings so don't worry if you are expecting silver for some reason. I was happy with the scent, but there was definitely a talcum powder type smell that lingered longer than the other scents. Could just be how it wears on my skin though. Bought a bottle from Kohl's also and the only difference between them is that when I put in the batch numbers the Kohl's one was 3 months fresher, but both were made within the last 6 months so doesn't matter. Overall this was an amazing price for a great perfume that I will wear quite often.

title: My first cologne, and it smells AMAZING
text:
This is the first cologne I ever owned. Before this, I was never a cologne wearer. One day, a few friends recommended this specific cologne to me, so I looked it up and I decided to try it out. After using it, I don't think I could be any more pleased with it. It's hard for me to compare with other colognes obviously since I'm not expert with this being my first. I will say, though, that I now own two other colognes, Nautica Blue and some Lacoste cologne that I don't remember the name of, and neither of them even compare to this one.

I was skeptical when my friends first recommended this to me, because I didn't think I would use it enough to justify the purchase. But since it was only $17, I decided to go ahead and get it. On a normal day I'll use one of my other two colognes, but for special days, I'm sure to use this one because it smells so amazing. If you're looking for a cologne that smells terrific, I definitely recommend this product. And if you end up not liking it, it's only $17, which is a pretty good investment if you ask me.

title: The price is ridiculously low, for all that I get out of it!
text:
Whenever I wear this and seemingly wherever I go, whether it be to work at the hospital, to the dentist office, to shopping, I have received compliments on this fragrance. It has such an airy, pleasant, fresh, clean, aquatic scent to it. It's versatile, for it can be worn anywhere and at anytime of the day or night. And I imagine as much as you want, because no one I encountered found it overpowering, no matter if pumped on one spray, or six. I find myself even complimenting myself when I wear it, "[expletive omitted] do I smell good!"

I can tell you that it is just so nice to hear people being able to value the things that I value, whether it be books or music charming us both, even a fragrance - for mutual value affinity and visibility I seek out in others. This fragrance gives me that, finding others out there who like what I like, and say so to me.

The price is ridiculously low, compared to all the value that I receive as a direct result of others valuation of it, how much I personally value it, and how much it is sold here for, compared to how much I have seen department stores sell the same size for.

I highly recommend it.

title: Can Smell This Next Day - Longevity for Your Entire Voyage
text:
Longevity is something you search for in a designer fragrance, and Nautica Voyage delivers. One to three sprays of this scent, and you'll be able to smell it the next day. Seriously. I have smelled and tested hundreds of colognes, and Voyage is near the top for a lasting fragrance. This lasts longer than Chrome or even Obsession. 1 Million might last a bit longer.

You get this fantastic long lasting scent from the minuscule amount that the sprayer puts out. After all, that's why we buy expensive cologne, right? See for yourself. Go to a store. Spray a fragrance card. Smell that card in a day or two, and it will still smell like Voyage.

Spectacular aquatic scent. Fresh and clean. Somewhat akin to Cool Water, but better, and oh so long lasting. Nautica makes many appealing aquatic fragrances. This is my favorite. Find it in retail stores for $30+ an ounce, then come to Amazon for a better price on a wonderful product.

title: but it has some cool twists that others do not have
text: Summertime in a bottle, plain and simple.  It is a straight-up fresh aquatic fragrance, but it has some cool twists that others do not have.  It has this nice melon/apple note that is a good change-up from the citrus that most summertime aquatic fragrances are centered around.  There is a nice salty air scent as well.  The longevity is SUPERB for a fresh fragrance that is this cheap; it easily lasts eight+ hours on me.  It is not really a suit and tie scent per se, but if you want something relaxing to wear casually, this one is excellent, although you can pull it off at the office well during summertime.  It is a little too beachy for wintertime for my tastes, but if you want to smell like the beach all year round, what is wrong with that?  Oh yeah, and this one will get you compliments left and right.  I have some fragrances that cost six times as much as Nautica Voyage that have not gotten me nearly as many compliments.  For the price, you absolutely cannot go wrong, especially for summer.  My favorite Nautica fragrance.

title: MELONS
text: I bought this cologne on clearance at Marshalls for around $10 and at first hated it. I was not expecting to get a fruity cologne. It was definitely a blind buy and I regretted buying it for the longest time. This was before I learned about the dry-down period of colognes. After a while, they interact with your skin and can change completely in terms of smell. This is one of the colognes that I've tried that does this. At first, you are bombarded by the scent of melons. I mean extremely sweet melons...and a lot of them. After it dries down, it is still very sweet and fruity but the melon dies down a bit and blends with some of the other notes to produce the perfect summer day fragrance. I could wear this walking on the beach in the middle of June and reapply it before going to a barbecue that night. It is very versatile within the warmer seasons. Absolute recommendation from me if you enjoy sweeter fragrances.

title: One of the finest perfumes available for men
text: I have been using davidoff coolwater and curve since a very long time. These are the kinds which literally get you compliments every time you wear them. I was kinda getting tired of them myself since I have been using them for more than 2 years ( switching between them ). I wanted something different which would be long lasting also and I love smelling clean,fresh and good. So I decided to give 'Nautica voyage' a try and was super-impressed. It has got a clean fresh smell which when sits on the skin for sometime gives wonderful after notes. I rate a perfume by my personal test. If you wear it in the morning ( specific pressure points on your body will give you the maximum effect ) and you can smell the light notes of it next morning on the clothes you wore yesterday, thats the mark of an awesome perfume. Nautica voyage passed that personal test and i'm happy that I found another compliment catcher and at least a temporary distraction from coolwater and curve which are still my personal favorites and always be. Definitely worth the price.

title: Definitely worth the money and offers Longevity and a very safe/fresh masculine scent.
text: I would most strongly recommend this product for high school/college individuals who are beginning to understand the importance of good fragrances but are restricted in terms of money.  I was there once too!  However, this fragrance does not smell cheap in any regard and holds an integrity that is very clean and sharp. What I love so much about this fragrance is its longevity.  On clean, remotely moist skin it will last 8-12 hours.  It is also fairly potent for an aquatic fragrance, so easy on the trigger, two-three sprays on chest/neck will do it.  It opens its top-notes with a fruity presence that smells likes apples and settles quickly into a fresh/clean/floral green accord and settles its base in a very pleasant and masculine woody/aquatic contrast.  I find, like most aquatic fragrances it is best appreciated during the late spring/summer seasons.  For the price and quality this fragrance is hard to beat.  I was an avid wearer in my high school years and have been through many fragrances.  I still have profound respect and continue to come back with reliance to this one. Pick it up now, and remember to purchase through Amazon LLC. instead of a third party selling on Amazon to ensure authenticity.

title: Great, long lasting scent
text:
I was never much of a cologne wearer, perhaps some Old Spice back in college decades ago, but I wanted to see what was available. After sampling opinions from some women friends, I decided to order Nautica Voyage from Amazon. To be honest, I had never heard of the product until just recently and when my wife and I visited the local mall to get a sniff test, there were no salespeople at the mens cologne section for me to test before ordering. As a result, I purchased this product on a hope that it would not be bad.

I can tell you that I am so very pleased with this product. It smells great, the ladies at work all enjoy it, and the smell last all day. With a limited experience in wearing men's cologne, I was not really sure how or where to apply this stuff with the little spray bottle, but have learned that one puff spray on my chest, under my shirt, works great and is not overpowering.

You cannot go wrong with this product. It is a romantic scent while still smelling manly if you will.

I will purchase again but with the size of the bottle and how little I need to smell great, it will be some time before I need to order again.

title: without great pretensions does what it has to do and in ...
text:
Nautica Voyage, is proof that you can still have hope in the perfume industry, without great pretensions does what it has to do and in an extraordinary way.

Its green opening makes me remember the smell of leaves wet by rain, immediately the green apple explodes with a very subtle sweetness, this initial combination is what I think gives so much life and energy to the fragrance.

During the drying it is possible to appreciate a little the cedar, but nothing that surprises.

Its longevity is over 6 hours and its projection is great, you have to be a little careful with the over application especially if your stage is indoors.

Nautica Voyage is extremely simple and easy to use and right there is its charm, suitable for tod @ s, excellent in summer and meeting in intermediate stations, the price relation is indisputable.

title: Doubting it's authenticity
text:
At first I was pretty happy with this purchase. It smelled nice and while I noticed the scent only lasted an hour or two, I got a 3.4 ounce bottle when I only paid for a 1.7 ounce bottle and I paid like 1/3 normal retail price.

The other day while shopping at a department store, I saw this cologne at the fragrance counter. I gave it a quick spray on my wrist (free cologne!) and noticed it was much stronger and more pleasant than mine. The single spray also lasted longer than the 2-3 I usually use.

I'm seriously starting to believe I received a knock-off. The price is almost too good and the scent isn't as good as the stuff from the department store. Amazon should look into this.

title: Fake Fake Fake - cmon Amazon when did you get into this business...
text:
I have bought quite a few perfumes from Amazon and sometimes from its affiliates. And many a times, I doubted the Authenticity of the perfumes. After buying this one from Amazon direct, my doubts are now confirmed.

I have the exact same bottle from a departmental store, it seems in the originals, the shrink-wraps can be opened from the sides as well. In this case(fake), only from the top or bottom (for easy repackage of return items or demos). I learned that from an expert.

Second, the sticker on the bottom of the perfume bottle came off very easily and I could not spot any serial number info either. A very good sign. In the originals, the stickers are very difficult to peel off.

And most important test is of course the smell. And the very first few sprays, I knew this was a fake. Smelled nothing but alcohol. What ever little smell it had faded in 1-2 hours. The original one from the dept store lasts for a 8-10 hrs if not more.

Someone in law enforcement needs to do something about this. This is getting out of hand if companies like Amazon knowingly or unknowingly are doing this. I have now serious doubts about my Bvlgari Aqua and Armani Aqua de Jio as well. Coz when I had tried them on at the local store, I remember they lasting quite long and the ones I actually purchased from Amazon (direct) for half price hardly makes it through the day.

Gosh, I am a perfume freak and have bought at least 15-20 diff perfumes for me and my wife in the last 2 years from Amazon and its affiliate alone. How many of these are fakes !?

title: Sea In A Bottle
text:
The perfumer behind this, Maurice Roucel, and the company, Nautica, gave a gem/gift to the world. This is a very easy to wear cologne and with the performance to back it up at such a great price. I do wonder if somehow Nautica turns a profit on these. Any way, once I get out of the shower I spray 1 on the chest and 1 on each side of the neck and I get 8 hours with decent projection *5 feet* and sillage. Take into account that where I live it tends to be around warm and somewhat hot all year round, so take that into consideration for the performance I got out of it.

The subject line pretty much describes what you get on this bottle. Wear it especially on warm/days and it'll start changing into different sea scents. Naturally, the hotter it gets the more beastly it'll be. There are other fragrances around this price points and even more expensive one's that don't accomplish what Nautica Voyage does. I do admit that the third day of wearing it I got the mysterious cat urine smell that some people on basenotes talked about (LOL). If i did detect it, it was way in the background. You really had to be looking for it and of course have previous knowledge about I just did to you right now :p

I'd say try it out first if you're into those kinds of aquatic scents. Cheapy but a goodie.

This is my second bottle of Nautica Voyage. The first one was a 1.7oz bottle from Kohls for $34.99. So when I searched Amazon and found this deal for double that amount (3.4 oz) for $18.30 after tax. I read some of the reviews that they had received an imposter cologne because the cap was plastic.

Well let me tell you those reviews are bogus. The cap design likely had changed since they last purchased because the look of the cap, scent, and strength. It was exactly what was expected... Nautica Voyage! Don't believe those reviews and take advantage of this unbeatable deal!
Smells great and real

title: Compliment on First Day!
text:
Was looking for a clean/refreshing fragrance. While I thought about purchasing 'Invictus Aqua', this was a very cheap alternative with great reviews. So I said "why not?".

To my surprise, it has a VERY clean, refreshing scent to it. When you wear this, you bring a wonderful crisp smell into the dull, scentless room! And yes, people notice it too.

Recieved a compliment from a female co-worker the first day I wore it, asked me what I was wearing. Like I said, it's a nice scent!

Scent is A+. Projection lasts about 3-4 hours, afterwards being less strong but still noticable up close. Total longevity is about 6 hours since it's a light fragrance, not too shabby.

Total recommend. If you don't like it, throw it in the corner. It's too affordable to not AT LEAST try first.

title: It's cologne I suppose. Not something I would buy again or recommend
text:
Perhaps I got one of the fabled fakes or bad bottles? The one I got seems completely legit to me, and the scent is very disappointing, though maybe not objectively "bad".

I bought this in 2016 because I was looking for a starting point into cologne, and this is clearly one of the most highly rated on Amazon. I was looking for something light, not alcohol-y, and very aquatic / clean smelling. Unfortunately, the bottle that I got is actually very strong (in a bad way, for me), does smell quite heavily of alcohol, and while I can definitely get a hint of the aquatic aspect that the cologne purportedly has, it's hugely overshadowed by the heavy musk of whatever else is in there.

Initially, I thought this was just a shock because I'm not used to wearing cologne. I would first wear a little bit around the house to see how it set into my skin over time, thinking it would eventually get good (perhaps just the top note was bad?). Eventually I started to wear a very trace amounts to work to try to adjust to it, eventually going down to one single spray on one wrist. Even this was too heavy and musky, and funnily enough, did last all day, and ended up giving me a slight headache. I felt embarrassed to have it on, in fear that other people may be smelling what I was smelling. After this, I stopped using it altogether.

As a funny anecdote, I had a rather unpleasant repeat customer at my workplace that would come in wearing this stuff every single time - I could tell it was this scent without an ounce of doubt. Eventually my coworkers would start comment on his "terrible" cologne after he came in, and I could actually tell if he had been in because of the heavy scent cloud that would persist when he came by. I'll chalk most of this up to the guy probably using WAY too much cologne in general, but experiencing this scent on someone else definitely solidified my thoughts about it not being something I ever want to wear again.

Overall, I gave it 2 stars instead of 1, because maybe I just have the exact chemistry required to dislike this cologne, and it's definitely not the worst thing I've ever smelled. It's also a very fair price, and does seem to last a while (even though I think I dislike the base notes the most). However, this is something I'd recommend you go into a store to try first, as if I had done so myself, I definitely would not have bought an entire bottle of this. Additionally, by doing this, you may come across a bottle of what, in my head, this scent was actually "supposed" to smell like and decide accordingly (apparently there was a reformulation, and perhaps a lot of fakes. Hard to tell with scents though).

title: My go-to
text:
Purchasing cologne online can be a scary experience, as there isn't a sniff test that can be performed. I decided to go out on a limb over a year ago and purchase this cologne, along with a couple others, based solely on their reviews. The Nautica Voyage is a winner for sure! I am now on my third bottle, and get compliments quite frequently on this cologne.

This is a light, clean scented cologne, which is strong, but certainly far from overpowering. It wears very well, and is hard to make it overpowering in any amount short of simply dumping the bottle on you. I am a fan of having cologne be discovered, not announced, and this fits that role perfectly. A few squirts are enough for the day, wearing all day on clothes, and probably 6-8 hours on skin. It has a clean smell, with strong notes of green apple, and reminds me of something similar to clean laundry on a warm spring day. It has a range of probably 5-10 feet when fresh (less than two hours old), and can be smelled from just over an arm's length away for most of the day. It is a hit with many women. I am a young male, (18-21), and I received comments on how I smell and get asked what I wear at least once a week.

It's served me well for over a year, and cannot be beat at the price. I am on my third bottle, and have two more stocked up! A bottle lasts me 4-6 month of daily wear, with two applications (morning, and again before going out at night).

title: Been using different colognes and this one seems to get a lot of good reaction. I am a waiter so of coarse ...
text:
I've bought tons of stuff from Amazon, including cologne. This is only my second review I'm making because this is one incredible deal. Been using different colognes and this one seems to get a lot of good reaction. I am a waiter so of coarse I like to smell nice, and this cologne has had guests genuinely laughing while telling me I smell so good. My coworkers have all complimented it to an extreme. Cool Water has always been my favorite, but people seem to really like this.

I can say it's legit, but it doesn't last forever. I guess it peeks shortly after you put it on and lasts for roughly 5-6 hours before the smell starts to vanquish.

Overall, for the price... WOW. This cologne is a keeper in my collection as I don't like to wear the same everyday.

Side note- the bottle and cap are my favorite out of all the colognes I use, very nice job there. Awesome stuff.

title: I should've listened
text:
With so many high reviews that this product got, I completely ignored the handful of them that warned of theories that it may be a tampered with product. I mean, how can something with 100+ reviews that mostly ships directly from Amazon be a knockoff. Well, a week in to owning this, and I'm 90% sure this is not a legit bottle of Nautica Voyage cologne.

The first day or two was amazing. The cologne smells extremely fresh and aquatic and lasted all the way through the day without issue. I was actually able to smell it clearly on my shirt at the end of the day. That all changed by the 3rd use. The smell was still good, but seemed not as potent and dissipated drastically about 15 minutes after application, at least compared to how it was the first few times. This morning came as shock. Out of curiosity, I sprayed it on at took a deep whiff. The smell was pure alcohol, a sort of vodka smell, and then only a slight hint of the actual cologne. It's now a few hours later, and I do smell the cologne on my shirt, but it's a fraction of what it should be.

Essentially, I think I got what I paid for: a $15 bottle of cologne. It truly does seem that the spray and tube did indeed have the actual cologne in it when I first got it, but the liquid in the bottle has been watered down with some alcohol. I'll continue to use this for work, because in it's preset form, it's extremely subtle and not intrusive. However, I can't wear it for special occasions or nights out. It's nothing more to me than a decent knockoff. It unfortunately is worth it's discounted price and not a penny more. Do yourself a favor, pony up a few more bucks and buy your cologne from a reliable brick and mortar store, lest you run the risk of getting a tampered with bottle like me.

title: Excellent Product; Shipping Concern
text:
This Nautica Voyage cologne has an amazing scent. When you spray it, it lasts for a long time. Usually a spray or two on the neck or wrist will make it last much longer than on clothing because the heat from your arteries and the sweat on your skin complement and amplify the scent.

Pros:
The cologne lasts a very long time
The cologne has an aquatic scent mixed with some citrus accents and musk.

Cons:
The only thing I would add is that buyers should be aware that cologne is made of chemicals and can change it's scent when exposed to warm temperatures and light. I bought this in the summer so when I got the cologne, it was quite warm to the touch. Some colognes smell downright nasty after being in the heat but as for this one, it still smelled good.

title: Great value for thr dollar, but the incosistency is dissapointing
text: Came as promised, cheap, but good cologne. Honestly, there is fowl play about with the 'Voyage' series. I've gotten it from multiple vendors and have received 2 different kinds of bottles, slightly varied but the same name. One has a more quality feel, and thus a sweeter, more quality scent. The other (the one that I received) has a cheaper, plastic cap, and a more harsh, alcoholy scent to it. Again, both are boxed the same under the same line. I don't know if its just the bad batch that they sell off for cheap or what, but very annoying when its a guessing game as to what I'm getting. Both smell good, but there's an obvious inconsistency in final product. 2 stars for playing a guessing game when it comes to that, super frustrating, especially when you only know after you unbox it.

title: Nice Floral Fruity Scent
text:
This has got to be the most perfect scent for summer! Its a very nice fruity, soapy floral scent and since there is no citrus in it like typical aquatics, it is not harsh at all and very very pleasant to the nose. And when I say floral, it does that mean that it smells feminine at all, it just has that just hoped out of the shower fresh feeling. The best way for to describe it is think of like a nice fresh body wash and makes you feel fresh and clean, this is pretty much that smell.
This cologne gets raved on by basenotes and fragantica as being one of the "best cheapie" fragrances you can get. Longevity and sillage are also pretty impressive as well for an aquatic (6-7 hours on my skin). Definitely a fragrance for a younger guy in high school or college.

title: Refreshing Men's Fragrance.
text: Nautica Voyage Eau De Toilette for Men is an absolute gem! This fragrance has captured my heart with its fresh, romantic, and fruity scent that perfectly balances elegance and masculinity. The blend of woody and aquatic notes, including apple, water lotus, cedarwood, and musk, creates an invigorating aroma that uplifts my mood and leaves a lasting impression. It's the ideal companion for daytime wear, enhancing my confidence and attracting compliments wherever I go. The 3.3 Fl Oz size ensures long-lasting enjoyment, making this fragrance an excellent investment. I highly recommend Nautica Voyage Eau De Toilette for Men to anyone seeking a captivating scent that embodies sophistication and charm.

title: A fresh fragrance with fantastic value
text:
First off, bought this directly from Amazon and it is the real thing. In my experience, if Amazon is the seller there is almost never an issue with perfumes.

Given the price, this is an absolutely fantastic deal for a 3.4oz (100ml) bottle of fragrance. The best description I can give of the smell is that it is fresh. However, It is not like some of the summer fragrances which have citrus notes in them (e.g. CK one summer). The closest it is to the perfumes I have used would be Echo by Davidoff.

Buying fragrances online is always a challenge so I'll list some other perfumes I use and like so that you may get an idea of my taste. Generally I like fragrances that are fresh and/or citrusy.

Some I like - L'eau D'issey by Issey Miyake, Chrome by Azzaro, Acqua Di Gio by Giorgio Armani, Cool Water by Davidoff, CK One , CK One Summer, CK Eternity

Don't like - Dunhill Red, CK obsession

title: Excellent Scent, if you like the style
text:
I honestly purchased this due to the great price a few weeks ago, and had never smelled it previously. I read the reviews and just couldn't pass up the deal.

I'm extremely happy that I didn't pass on it. This has become one of my favorite colognes, and it is now in heavy rotation along with Armani Code.

This is a 'water' cologne, and some people just don't like that style...and that's just fine. I love the style, and think this is one of the best smelling colognes in it.

It's also quite long lasting. I generally apply it before work, and it's still noticeable when I'm getting home ~10 hours later(at very close distance)

All in all, a great scent that I'm really glad I jumped on. I jumped at an even cheaper price on Nautica Blue, and while I'm not as enamored with the scent, it's not too bad.

title: Canâ€™t go wrong
text:
Nautica Voyage is an exceptional cologne that exudes a refreshing and invigorating scent, perfect for those seeking an active fragrance. From the moment you apply it, youâ€™re greeted with a burst of citrusy notes, like crisp green apple and zesty bergamot, which instantly awaken your senses.

What sets Nautica Voyage apart is its ability to maintain its lively character throughout the day. The heart of the fragrance unfolds with a subtle blend of aquatic notes, giving it a distinctively fresh and clean vibe. Itâ€™s reminiscent of a cool ocean breeze, leaving you feeling rejuvenated and ready to conquer the day.

One of the standout aspects of Nautica Voyage is its excellent value for the size. With a generous bottle, you get a lot of cologne for your money, making it a worthwhile investment. The longevity is impressive as well, as the scent lingers on the skin for hours without fading away.

I particularly enjoy wearing Nautica Voyage during outdoor activities and warm weather. Its energetic and sporty essence perfectly complements an active lifestyle. Whether youâ€™re heading to the gym or spending a day by the beach, this cologne is a fantastic choice to accompany your endeavors.

Overall, Nautica Voyage is a captivating fragrance that combines an active scent with great value. Its refreshing notes and long-lasting performance make it a go-to option for those who appreciate a vibrant and invigorating fragrance. Give it a try, and let the captivating journey of Nautica Voyage begin.

I hope this review captures the essence of Nautica Voyage and helps you in sharing your thoughts on this fantastic cologne!

title: Not the Same, but worth the price!
text:
I've been wearing this perfume for a long time and I've always loved it but refused to pay $50 for a small bottle in store. I went to by my mom perfume and thought to buy this since I already had free shipping. I was skeptical because I know a lot of perfumes so cheap from their store counterparts are fake or watered down.
The first spray of this perfume on my skin I knew it wasn't the perfume I've been wearing for years. I was really sad and debating if I should deal with the return or just use it because it didn't smell that bad and would still be a perfume I would wear. But after I had the perfume on for an hour or so and started moving around the smell of the in store Vera Wang Princess perfume was noticeable and the smell straight out the bottle was gone. There is still something different (like the perfume smells sweeter than normal) but not so different that I would spend $50+ on the perfume in store.
My perfume is the same light purple color of the perfume and the bottle is the same. The only thing I notice about the bottle is that the ring at the top of the bottle that makes the base of the princess crown came off with the top. But super glue can fix that, not a deal breaker.

title: perfect summer cologne
text: I have always been an avid cologne consumer. my signature scent as of the past year has been BVLGARI man Extreme. And while that still is my favorite cologne, my bottle ran dry about a week ago. I had a first date planned with this girl, and i kind of forgot until she reminded me, and i thought "oh crap i dont have cologne". i was right near my local retail store, and i ran in. No BVLGARi. so i asked for some help from the girl working and she recommended this fragrance. when i first tried it on i wasnt too impressed, but impressed enough to get the 1.7oz bottle since i just needed SOMETHING. i put it on after my grooming regimen and ran out the door. by the time i got to the girls apartment to pick her up, the scent had seemingly settled into a much more clean/fresh aquatic scent that i really enjoyed. by the end of the night i had received a very nice compliment about my smell. so i highly recommend it for a nice summer day/night fragrance. and for the price, you just cant beat it.

title: Beautiful perfume.
text: This is my first time trying the Vera Wang Princess perfume. I decided to give it a try based on good reviews, a lot of people seem to really love the perfume. Also the fact that I could get it for such a good price and havenâ€™t had perfume in a while so why not?! I had read others bad reviews on the product and was worried this would be a fake. But after 2 full days of wearing it, Iâ€™m pretty sure it is the real thing. It lasts at least 8 hours on my skin, and has no alcohol scent, nor is it watered down. It has that deep, velvety scent that I love and reminds me of other legitimate perfumes I have had in the past. The scent is lovely, and just as described: fruity, floral with notes of amber and vanilla. I mostly smell the floral and almost a musky but feminine scent. I really do like it, my hubby has even complimented it. I think itâ€™s a beautiful bottle and a really good size. Also, the packaging is so cute. Overall I would definitely recommend this perfume.

title: Better than Expected
text: Ive bought several types of name brand colognes through amazon that turned out to be watered down fakes in the name brand bottles, but this one was completely legitimate.  Its a really nice aquatic summery fragrance with hints of cucumber, melon, and seaweed to start, then the scent changes to a more fresh smelling musk after a couple hours.  The scent sticks on you all day, which is more than i can say about some of the disappointing fakes ive bought off amazon in the past... Trust me, you cant go wrong with this one.  People will make excuses to stand near you just so they can smell it, very nice smell.

title: Super Exciting and Refreshing Smell for Summer and Spring!!
text:
Nautica Voyage is a fresh, aquatic fragrance for men that was launched in 2006. It is a popular choice for everyday wear and is known for its clean, refreshing scent.

The top notes of Nautica Voyage are apple, grapefruit, and bergamot. The heart notes are water lotus, cedarwood, and sage. The base notes are musk and amber.

Nautica Voyage is a versatile fragrance that can be worn for a variety of occasions. It is perfect for casual wear, work, or a night out. The fragrance is also long-lasting and will keep you smelling fresh all day long.

Here are some of the pros and cons of Nautica Voyage Eau De Toilette for Men:

Pros:

Fresh, aquatic scent
Clean, refreshing
Versatile
Long-lasting
Affordable
